						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/UN-adopts-resolution-on-agricultural-technology-for-development" title="UN adopts resolution on agricultural technology for development" alt="link">UN adopts resolution on agricultural technology for development</a></h2>

	
					<p> The UN General Assembly has adopted an Israeli-initiated draft resolution dealing with agricultural technology for development. The resolution calls on developed countries to make their knowledge and know-how in the field of agricultural technology more accessible to the developing world, in particular for the eradication of extreme poverty and hunger. The UN Secretary General is required to submit a report to the General Assembly on its implementation within two years. The resolution gives expression to Israeli know-how in the areas of agriculture, fighting desertification, rural development, irrigation, medical development, computers and the empowerment of women, as reflected for many years in Israel's contribution to developing nations, particularly in Africa. Source: Israel MFA, 11 December 2007.</p>
							<p><span class="date">7/01/2008</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/UN-adopts-resolution-on-agricultural-technology-for-development">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
